Task 1: Implement the B.J. Fogg Behavior Model
Understanding the Fogg Model
The B.J. Fogg Behavior Model states: B = MAT (Behavior occurs when Motivation, Ability, and Trigger converge)

Motivation: Desire to perform the behavior (0-10 scale)
Ability: Capacity to perform the behavior (0-10 scale)
Trigger: Prompt that initiates the behavior (0-10 scale)
